', '27/11/23, 2:14 pm - +263 77 630 8547: I wanted to ask om the issue of payment of tuiton 
', 'In the case that she gets the chance to be an Edoofian is it mandatory that the tuiton be paid in cash
', '27/11/23, 3:07 pm - Shubham Madhwal: @263776308547 the annual fee of the student which includes the remaining cost of tuition fees, food and accommodation expenses will have to be paid in semester wise which would be in installments of 6 months each that too after the student arrives at the University.
', '
', 'So for example, if after the scholarship the annual fee of the student comes to be let us say $2200, now to the University it has to be paid Semester Wise ( 2 Installments of 6 months each). Therefore it is paid like $1100 in the first semester and $1100 in the next semester, but there would be the Earn While You Learn Program which would help the student in reducing the semester fee as well.
', '
', 'Usually what parents do is, since after arriving in India students do get an Indian Bank Account opened, parents can also deposit the fee on a monthly basis into the students account and the student in one go can complete the semester fee after the interval of 6 months itself!
']
